Colleges.Name: George Mason University
Colleges.Summary: George Mason is a public university in Fairfax, VA. It is one of the most diverse and largest universities in VA. They offer more than 200 undergraduation and graduate degrees.

Colleges.Name: Virginia Tech
Colleges.Summary: Virginia Tech is a public university in Blacksburg, VA. It is known for its beautiful campus and large engineering field in the area

Colleges.Name: University of Virginia
Colleges.Summary: University of Virginia is a public university in Charlottesville, VA. It is known for their statistics and economic programs

Colleges.Name: James Madison University
Colleges.Summary: James Madison is a public university in Harrisonburg, VA. They have one of the best musical theater BA programs as well as bsuiness.

Colleges.Name: Virginia Commonwealth University
Colleges.Summary: Virginia Commonwealth is a public university in Richmond, VA. They are most popular for their fine arts and research programs. Their Medical Center is one of the top hospitals in Virginia.

Colleges.Name: William & Mary
Colleges.Summary: W&M is a public university in Williamsburg, VA. It is known as the second-oldest higher education institution. It has more than 30 undergraduate programs.
